result.execSummary:
The defendant Quintin J. Armbrust was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Fail/Report to Jail (Misdemeanor), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.425(1r)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Quintin J. Armbrust in court, in custody with attorney Alexander Paul Seifert.  Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls 14CF193, 15CM61 & 16CM110  @ 3:09  pm. State gives plea agreement, 184 days credit, State received revocation summary packet, no corrections.  3-6 months jail on 14CF193 and 3 months 15CM61. 16CM110 ct 2 DRI, Ct plea 30 days jail consecutive, costs.   Atty Seifert agrees with agreement.  Atty Seifert received revocation summary packet, no corrections.  Plea questionnaire and waiver of rights filed.  Def. understand charge and penalties. Ct 1 Failure to report to jail, no contest plea. Ct 2 DRI. Def. advised of constitutional rights & J.T. rights.  Def. understands elements.  Atty Seifert is satisfied.  Court finds plea is freely & voluntarily given.  Factual basis stipulated.  Court finds factual basis, accepts plea and finds def. Guilty to Failure to report to Jail. State gives sentencing recommendation.  Atty Seifert gives sentencing recommendation.  Def. has nothing to say.  Court orders
14CF193 ct 1 6 months jail, 
Ct 3 30 days jail, concurrent to ct 1
15CM61 30 days jail, concurrent to 14CF193
Court costs converted to civil judgment. 184 days credit, served.
16CM110 - Ct 1- 30 days jail, consecutive to other sentences. Credit from other cases, Time served, so probably completed, 200 DNA Surcharge, costs. Def. given p.p. $50 a month 1st payment due 2-1-17. Huber privileges.  Def. advised of postconviction rights.

Defendant Quintin J. Armbrust in court with attorney Jessica L Schuster.  Defendant Quintin J. Armbrust in custody.  Galen Bayne-Allison appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Bayne-Allison.  Warrant vacated by court.  Complaint received, reviewed and waive reading.  Not guilty pleas entered.  Court will receive not guilty pleas.  Bond recommendations by State.  Def is on probation hold.  Court sets bond.  Status conference scheduled for November 21, 2016 at 03:30 pm.
